				<exercise workspace="4in">
                    <title>Problems</title>
						<statement>
							<p>
								For each of the following, explain why the given description does not define a function.
<ol>
  <li>
    <p>
      <m>f:\{1,2,3\} \to \{1,2,3\}</m>, <m>f(a) = a-1</m>.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      <m>g: \mathbb{N}\to \mathbb{Q}</m>, <m>g(n) = \frac{n}{n-1}</m>.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      Let <m>A_{1} = \{1,2,3\}</m> and <m>A_{2} = \{3,4,5\}</m>.
      Define <m>h: A_{1} \cup A_{2} \to \{1,2\}</m> by
      <me>
        h(x) = \begin{cases}1,&#x26;\text{if }x \in A_{1} \\ 2,&#x26;\text{if }x \in A_{2}\end{cases}
      </me>
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      <m>s: \mathbb{Q}\to \mathbb{Z}</m>, <m>s(a/b) = a + b</m>.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>
							</p>
